Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a brown pottery vessel, the fabric is grey and red in section, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of at least six lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no.3(p.95,pl.xciii))
Jasnow & Pouls Wegner 2006-2007 / Demotic Ostraca from North Abydos (p.49)
Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393856) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393856)
